boolean.comment: The type is an object wrapper for the boolean primitive data type
boolean.name: Boolean

signed_integer_as_object.comment: The type is an object wrapper for the bigint primitive data type
signed_integer_as_object.name: Signed object-based Integer

signed_float_64_bit.comment: The Number wrapper object is represented by a double-precision 64-bit float under the hood. All the 'Not-a-Number' values in the IEEE Standard specification are clubbed into a single special NaN value in javascript.
signed_float_64_bit.name: Signed 64-bit floating point

signed_float_as_object.comment: The type is an object wrapper for the number primitive data type
signed_float_as_object.name: Signed object-based floating point

string_as_object.comment: The type is an object wrapper for the string primitive data type
string_as_object.name: String as an object

string_as_array.comment: String is implemented as a set of ordered sequences of zero or more 16-bit unsigned integer values (each treated as UTF-16 code unit). String objects support [index] notation to dereference characters, but do not support the full spectrum of array methods
string_as_array.name: String as an array of characters
